children.subject: The idea of a swap is such that whether you’re swapping a lecture or a division/lab section, if you can’t get into the target, you still get to keep your original class or section.

Uh.... I’m trying to drop Stat C100, which is the class I’m enrolled in, because I no longer want to take it. This means the other class involved (CS186) in the swap will be the class I remain on the waitlist for, per the website. However, if I add 70 to my schedule, will 70 and 186 be locked in a swap or are the two not involved with each other? Only 100 and 186 should be involved with each other permanently right?
Only 2 classes are involved in a swap.

Original poster: I just found this website and  dropping Stat C100 applies to case 3 underneath changes to swaps https://sis.berkeley.edu/help/enrollment-faq/swap
But if I add 70 will 70 be involved in swap?

history.content: I’m currently enrolled in CS61C, breadth, and Stat C100. I’m currently set another CS course (which I’m waitlisted in) to swap with Stat C100. I thought I was only enrolled in 12 units, but it turns out I’m enrolled in 16 units just by enrolling this way. (Even though I set this up during phase 1, which is strange because the swap setting should’ve been blocked during phase 1 since the cap is 13 units, and now I realized this incident). Now I’m trying to add CS70 during phase 2 and want to drop Stat c100 from calcentral, but I’m afraid that the swap setting would change to be such that the swap will drop me out of 70 What should I do? Is it safe to drop Stat C100 from calcentral without getting kicked out of the waitlist of my other class, and will dropping Stat c100 disable any swap request in this way? I don’t want to have to enroll in 70 during adjustment perriod
